summary: In one empire, it is said that the emperor and his wife were the two people who loved each other the most. It is said that the man loved his wife, he did not see anyone else, while she saw him as her only hope in life and everything. This love story was not because they met by chance and fell in love with each other at first sight. He loved her at first sight, while it took her a while to like him. That's what some books said. Other books said that they had a bad reputation and that they met once on his brother’s birthday and he caught a glimpse of her and admired her from afar, then he began to get closer to her. Actually this is all wrong. The true story is that His Majesty, when he was still the Crown Prince, went dragging the assassin sent to him by his half-brother to attend his birthday. There he met Penelope Eckart, who confessed her love to him. He did not know that this confession was just to avoid her being killed by him and to escape. But he stayed behind her, several times, until they fell in love with each other and got married after much difficulty.
